and GDR increased from 71.2 to 76.4 and from 1.04 to 1.08, respectively, 
worldwide. In the study period, countries of Western Europe, Scandinavia, and 
Australasia had the highest QCIs and a GDR of 1 to 1.2; however, African and 
South Asian countries had the lowest QCIs and a GDR of 0.8 to 1. Moreover, the 
young population experienced more significant improvements in the QCI compared 
to the elderly in 2017.
CONCLUSION: From 1990 to 2017, the QCI of IHD has improved; nonetheless, there 
are remarkable disparities between countries, genders, and age groups that 
should be addressed. These findings may guide policymakers in monitoring and 
modifying our path to achieve SDGs.

